<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1436,1626,2013]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
A Neotropical species whose larvae and nymphs are usually found on 
<taxonomicName box="[151,257,1662,1688]" class="Mammalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Rodentia</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[269,371,1662,1688]" class="Mammalia" family="Caviidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Caviidae</taxonomicName>
, but all known parasitic stages have been recovered from 
<taxonomicName box="[1035,1138,1662,1688]" class="Mammalia" family="Caviidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Caviidae</taxonomicName>
. Females alone have been collected from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Owen" authorityYear="1848" box="[323,468,1698,1724]" class="Mammalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Artiodactyla</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1821" box="[480,576,1698,1724]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Bovidae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Owen" authorityYear="1848" box="[639,805,1698,1724]" class="Mammalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Perissodactyla</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1821" box="[818,913,1698,1724]" class="Mammalia" family="Equidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Equidae</taxonomicName>
. There are no records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boero" authorityYear="1944" box="[1205,1436,1698,1724]" class="Arachnida" family="Ixodidae" genus="Ixodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ixodida" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiscutatus">
<emphasis box="[1205,1436,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Ixodes longiscutatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
causing human parasitism.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
